    <h1>Digimon Card Game Quick Start Guide</h1>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th colspan="2">The Four Types of Cards</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    Digimon Cards
                    <ul>
                        <li>Pay memory to play or digivolve them.</li>
                        <li>Digimon can attack.</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Digi-Egg Cards
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your Digi-Egg deck can have up to 5 cards.</li>
                        <li>Hatch or digivolve them in the Breeding Area.</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    Tamer Cards
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Once played, Tamers stay on the field and their effects remain active.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Option Cards
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            To play an Option card, you must have a Digimon or Tamer on the field of
